                <div>
                    <p>
                        Node-RED’s low code visual environment makes it easy for non-programmers to integrate data from different sources without needing to know how to code. 
                        Now, business departments can work on their own data integration projects without requiring IT support.

                    </p>
                 </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-left self-start">
                <h3>Support for <span class="text-red-600">Different Protocols</span></h3>
                <div>
                    <p>
                      By default, Node-RED supports the most common protocols for accessing data, including http, mqtt and websockets. The Node-RED community library has hundreds of nodes 
                      for specialized protocols, like Modbus, OPC-UA, Bachnet, etc.
                    </p>
                 </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-left self-start">
                <h3>Support for Different <span class="text-red-600">Data Formats</span></h3>
                <div>
                    <p>
                     Data is available in many different formats. By default Node-RED supports the following formats: csv, html, json, xml and yaml. 
                     Support for other data formats are available from the Node-RED library.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-left self-start">
                <h3><span class="text-red-600">Realtime</span> Data Visualization and Transformations</h3>
                <div>
                    <p>
                    Node-RED makes it easy to create real-time data visualizations and dashboards. Data in real-time can be filtered, transformed and analyzed through a Node-RED flow. 
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
